  "prompt": "How to add a link in a Quora answer to another Quora answer when using Quora iPhone app?",
  "response": "To add a link to another Quora answer within your Quora answer using the Quora iPhone app, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Open the Quora App**: Launch the Quora app on your iPhone.\n\n2. **Navigate to the Answer You Want to Link To**:\n   - Find the question and answer you want to link to. You can do this by searching for the question or navigating through the topic feeds.\n   - Tap on the answer to open it.\n\n3. **Copy the Link**:\n   - Once the answer is open, tap on the **Share** icon (it looks like an arrow pointing upward or a box with an arrow, depending on your iOS version).\n   - From the share options, choose **Copy Link**. This will copy the URL of the answer to your clipboard.\n\n4. **Compose Your Answer**:\n   - Go to the question where you want to write your answer.\n   - Start typing your answer in the text box.\n\n5. **Insert the Link**:\n   - Place your cursor where you want the link to appear in your answer.\n   - **Paste** the link by tapping and holding the text area and selecting **Paste** from the context menu.\n\n6. **Format the Link (Optional)**:\n   - If you want to make the link more user-friendly, you can replace the raw URL with descriptive text. For example, instead of pasting the full URL, you can type something like \"Check out this detailed answer,\" highlight the text, and then paste the link over it (this may require using the link formatting option if available).\n\n7. **Post Your Answer**:\n   - Review your answer to ensure everything looks correct.\n   - Tap the **Post** button to publish your answer with the link.\n\nBy following these steps, you can easily include a link to another Quora answer in your response using the Quora iPhone app.",
